                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d459">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/7560: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-08-17T10:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 17, 1926—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 17—6:14 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>328. My 317, August 5, noon. Following from American consul at Changsha: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Chiang Kai-shih arrived this morning. There is no serious fighting.
                            Earty renewal of drive toward Hankow is not unlikely. Department has not
                            been informed.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
